HEADWORD: Conjugal
<hw>Con"ju*gal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>conjugalis</ets>, fr. <ets>conjux</ets> husband, wife, consort, fr.
<ets>conjungere</ets> to unite, join in marriage. See
<er>Conjoin</er>.]</ety> <def>Belonging to marriage; suitable or
appropriate to the marriage state or to married persons; matrimonial;
connubial.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Conjugal</xex> affection.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

